    <div class="chapter reveal"><div class="num">Answered</div><div class="orn"><span class="d"></span></div><h2 id="faq">Frequently asked</h2></div>
    <h3 class="reveal">How much does it cost to automate a small online business?</h3>
    <p class="reveal">Less than you are afraid of. Make's free plan costs nothing, email platforms start free or under $15 a month at starter volume, and your checkout already delivers. The expensive version of automation is the one you buy before you need it.</p>
    <h3 class="reveal">Do I need to know how to code?</h3>
    <p class="reveal">No. Every automation here is built by clicking, connecting, and describing what you want. If you can build a Canva graphic, you can build a Make scenario. The skill is not technical — it is writing down your own steps clearly enough that a system can follow them.</p>
    <h3 class="reveal">How much should a beginner spend on ads?</h3>
    <p class="reveal">Ten dollars a day, and not more because you are excited. The budget is not the strategy — the pipeline is. It generates enough data to diagnose and enough subscribers to matter, while capping your worst week at seventy dollars. Scale by 10–20% only after ROAS proves the machine deserves it.</p>
    <h3 class="reveal">Can't AI just automate everything now?</h3>
    <p class="reveal">AI moves the line — it does not erase it. AI handles more repeatable work every month, and it is the single biggest lever in content production. But the caring tasks — community, support, judgment calls about real people — remain yours. The goal was never a business with no human in it. It is a business where the human only does human things.</p>
    <h3 class="reveal">When should I <em>not</em> automate something?</h3>
    <p class="reveal">When it touches a customer's actual problem, when you have not done it manually at least five times, or when the process still changes every run. Automating an unstable process manufactures mistakes at scale — you need a repeatable recipe before you hand it to a machine.</p>

